A Toyota Avanza that was stolen from Florida Road in Durban was recovered and abandoned in B Section, Umlazilast night. Police said a resident of Effingham Heights contacted Reaction Unit South Africa around 11pm requesting assistance to recover the vehicle. The police statement also states that the caller was monitoring the vehicle movements from an app on her cellphone. At the time of the call the vehicle was traveling on the N2 and heading towards Umlazi.Â It is also confirmed that the Toyota Avanza was fitted with a vehicle tracking device from Tracker which was also activated. Reaction Officers proceeded to the area and searched for the vehicle which was recovered by Tracker and the Umlazi SAPS. Police said suspects had fled and were not located. The number plates on the vehicle were changed and interior panels were striped. The computer box was also changed. The vehicle was impounded for further investigation.